"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Resistance\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Resistance\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"CGTN\", \"from\": 205, \"to\": 209}, {\"ngram\": \"the age\", \"from\": 220, \"to\": 227}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic torch\", \"from\": 268, \"to\": 285}, {\"ngram\": \"her fragile shoulder\", \"from\": 314, \"to\": 334}, {\"ngram\": \"the values\", \"from\": 348, \"to\": 358}, {\"ngram\": \"friendship\", \"from\": 362, \"to\": 372}, {\"ngram\": \"peoples\", \"from\": 381, \"to\": 388}, {\"ngram\": \"her time\", \"from\": 414, \"to\": 422}, {\"ngram\": \"the Second World War\", \"from\": 453, \"to\": 473}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A \\\"woman in the shadows\\\" during the Occupation (1940-1944), Berger-Volle was thrilled to be chosen to carry the torch as it passes through Saint-Etienne on June 22 on its way to Paris for the start of the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 478, \"to\": 697, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 617, \"end\": 630, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metz_Cathedral\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.427707072688879e-21, \"text\": \"Saint-Etienne\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q1370598\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metz_Cathedral\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metz_Cathedral\"}, {\"begin\": 656, \"end\": 661, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.1881768547217342e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A \\\"woman\", \"from\": 478, \"to\": 486}, {\"ngram\": \"the shadows\", \"from\": 490, \"to\": 501}, {\"ngram\": \"the Occupation\", \"from\": 510, \"to\": 524}, {\"ngram\": \"Berger-Volle\", \"from\": 538, \"to\": 550}, {\"ngram\": \"the torch\", \"from\": 586, \"to\": 595}, {\"ngram\": \"June\", \"from\": 634, \"to\": 638}, {\"ngram\": \"its way\", \"from\": 645, \"to\": 652}, {\"ngram\": \"the start\", \"from\": 666, \"to\": 675}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 679, \"to\": 696}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The weight of the torch has been a concern but there was never any question of turning it down.\", \"from\": 699, \"to\": 794, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The weight\", \"from\": 699, \"to\": 709}, {\"ngram\": \"the torch\", \"from\": 713, \"to\": 722}, {\"ngram\": \"a concern\", \"from\": 732, \"to\": 741}, {\"ngram\": \"any question\", \"from\": 762, \"to\": 774}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have always loved sport,\\\" says the sprightly centenarian who until recently enjoyed an hour's walk a day.\", \"from\": 796, \"to\": 904, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 817, \"to\": 822}, {\"ngram\": \"the sprightly centenarian\", \"from\": 830, \"to\": 855}, {\"ngram\": \"an hour's walk\", \"from\": 883, \"to\": 897}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Grandmother of the gymnast Emilie Volle, who took part in the Atlanta Olympics in 1996, she also wants to be a symbol for women \\\"who have fought to play sport like men\\\".\", \"from\": 906, \"to\": 1075, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 968, \"end\": 984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.1420529772001583e-13, \"text\": \"Atlanta Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the gymnast\", \"from\": 921, \"to\": 932}, {\"ngram\": \"Emilie Volle\", \"from\": 933, \"to\": 945}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 960}, {\"ngram\": \"a symbol\", \"from\": 1015, \"to\": 1023}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1033}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 1059, \"to\": 1064}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 1070, \"to\": 1073}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Melanie Berger-Volle, 102, will carry the Olympic torch later this year.\", \"from\": 1077, \"to\": 1149, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Melanie Berger\", \"from\": 1077, \"to\": 1091}, {\"ngram\": \"-Volle\", \"from\": 1091, \"to\": 1097}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic torch\", \"from\": 1115, \"to\": 1132}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/AFP \\\"My ideal has always been to unite the world,\\\" she says.\", \"from\": 1150, \"to\": 1212, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"My ideal\", \"from\": 1156, \"to\": 1164}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1190, \"to\": 1199}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"And the Olympics are a wonderful opportunity to get to know other human beings.\\\"\", \"from\": 1213, \"to\": 1294, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1230}, {\"ngram\": \"a wonderful opportunity\", \"from\": 1235, \"to\": 1258}, {\"ngram\": \"other human beings\", \"from\": 1274, \"to\": 1292}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Born in Austria in 1921 into a Jewish working-class family, Melanie Berger began her activism as a teenager in an extreme left-wing group.\", \"from\": 1296, \"to\": 1434, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1304, \"end\": 1311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_State_of_Austria\", \"score\": 0.9790605058025131, \"rank\": 0.02136701535167666, \"text\": \"Austria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_State_of_Austria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_State_of_Austria\"}, {\"begin\": 1327, \"end\": 1333, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jews\", \"score\": 0.8633171704587289, \"rank\": 0.13073592367186498, \"text\": \"Jewish\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jews\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jews\"}, {\"begin\": 1356, \"end\": 1363, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melanie_Griffith\", \"score\": 0.5085264710889972, \"rank\": 0.7469599327559292, \"text\": \"Melanie\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melanie_Griffith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melanie_Griffith\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her activism\", \"from\": 1377, \"to\": 1389}, {\"ngram\": \"a teenager\", \"from\": 1393, \"to\": 1403}, {\"ngram\": \"an extreme left-wing group\", \"from\": 1407, \"to\": 1433}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We were atheists and when I started fighting it wasn't for religious reasons, it was political,\\\" she says.\", \"from\": 1436, \"to\": 1543, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"atheists\", \"from\": 1445, \"to\": 1453}, {\"ngram\": \"religious reasons\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 1513}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am against all dictatorships.\\\"\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1577, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all dictatorships\", \"from\": 1558, \"to\": 1575}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After the annexation of Austria by Nazi Germany in 1938, she left her country, went to Belgium and then arrived in France, in Paris in the spring of 1939, disguised as a boy.\", \"from\": 1579, \"to\": 1753, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1603, \"end\": 1610, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_State_of_Austria\", \"score\": 0.9790605058025131, \"rank\": 0.02136701535167666, \"text\": \"Austria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_State_of_Austria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_State_of_Austria\"}, {\"begin\": 1614, \"end\": 1626, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9850621389650008, \"rank\": 0.01514319623840584, \"text\": \"Nazi Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 1666, \"end\": 1673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.56419423062749e-13, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 1694, \"end\": 1700, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9652333887712642, \"rank\": 0.019185769610298418, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1705, \"end\": 1710, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.1881768547217342e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the annexation\", \"from\": 1585, \"to\": 1599}, {\"ngram\": \"her country\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1656}, {\"ngram\": \"the spring\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1724}, {\"ngram\": \"a boy\", \"from\": 1747, \"to\": 1752}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When France went to war later that year, all Austrians, even refugees, were seen as enemies and the authorities put her on a train to a camp near Pau.\", \"from\": 1754, \"to\": 1904, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1759, \"end\": 1765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9652333887712642, \"rank\": 0.019185769610298418, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1799, \"end\": 1808, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austrians\", \"score\": 0.9999917799038005, \"rank\": 7.4459821473082e-06, \"text\": \"Austrians\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austrians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austrians\"}, {\"begin\": 1900, \"end\": 1903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Section_Paloise\", \"score\": 0.8187149216236455, \"rank\": 0.22141932305926715, \"text\": \"Pau\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Section_Paloise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Section_Paloise\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"war\", \"from\": 1774, \"to\": 1777}, {\"ngram\": \"even refugees\", \"from\": 1810, \"to\": 1823}, {\"ngram\": \"enemies\", \"from\": 1838, \"to\": 1845}, {\"ngram\": \"the authorities\", \"from\": 1850, \"to\": 1865}, {\"ngram\": \"a train\", \"from\": 1877, \"to\": 1884}, {\"ngram\": \"a camp\", \"from\": 1888, \"to\": 1894}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At Clermont-Ferrand station, she \\\"jumped out\\\" of the carriage.\", \"from\": 1906, \"to\": 1968, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Clermont-Ferrand station\", \"from\": 1909, \"to\": 1933}, {\"ngram\": \"the carriage\", \"from\": 1955, \"to\": 1967}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was on her own as the other girls did not dare follow her.\", \"from\": 1969, \"to\": 2031, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the other girls\", \"from\": 1991, \"to\": 2006}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They were not political, they did not know what a camp was,\\\" she shrugs.\", \"from\": 2033, \"to\": 2106, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a camp\", \"from\": 2082, \"to\": 2088}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the contrary, the young activist was well aware that \\\"when you get a chance, you can not let it go by.\\\"\", \"from\": 2107, \"to\": 2213, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the contrary\", \"from\": 2110, \"to\": 2122}, {\"ngram\": \"the young activist\", \"from\": 2124, \"to\": 2142}, {\"ngram\": \"a chance\", \"from\": 2177, \"to\": 2185}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris 2024 Olympic torch.\", \"from\": 2215, \"to\": 2244, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2219, \"end\": 2229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.383208732225468e-15, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"/AFP In 1940 after the French surrender to the Nazis, she found herself in Montauban, where a group of Trotskyist militants she had belonged to before the war was beginning to reform.\", \"from\": 2245, \"to\": 2429, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2269, \"end\": 2285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9639011966335128, \"rank\": 0.03745072990113248, \"text\": \"French surrender\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 2293, \"end\": 2298, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazism\", \"score\": 0.7785497880389073, \"rank\": 0.2766249248929567, \"text\": \"Nazis\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazism\"}, {\"begin\": 2321, \"end\": 2330, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montauban\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1548626551519847e-18, \"text\": \"Montauban\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montauban\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montauban\"}, {\"begin\": 2349, \"end\": 2359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trotskyism\", \"score\": 0.9999998651555961, \"rank\": 1.3484463963482774e-07, \"text\": \"Trotskyist\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trotskyism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trotskyism\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a group\", \"from\": 2337, \"to\": 2344}, {\"ngram\": \"the war\", \"from\": 2396, \"to\": 2403}, {\"ngram\": \"reform\", \"from\": 2421, \"to\": 2427}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"With my French-sounding name, I rented a flat in a dilapidated house, and from there we were able to start work.\\\"\", \"from\": 2431, \"to\": 2545, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my French-sounding name\", \"from\": 2437, \"to\": 2460}, {\"ngram\": \"a dilapidated house\", \"from\": 2481, \"to\": 2500}, {\"ngram\": \"work\", \"from\": 2539, \"to\": 2543}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Discreetly, the group drafted and distributed German-language leaflets aimed at turning Reich soldiers.\", \"from\": 2547, \"to\": 2650, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2593, \"end\": 2608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.324263954509113e-26, \"text\": \"German-language\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2635, \"end\": 2640, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9999999998981366, \"rank\": 9.142472213502296e-11, \"text\": \"Reich\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the group\", \"from\": 2559, \"to\": 2568}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But in January 1942 that all came to an end when the police raided the house and she was arrested and brutally interrogated.\", \"from\": 2651, \"to\": 2775, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"January\", \"from\": 2658, \"to\": 2665}, {\"ngram\": \"an end\", \"from\": 2688, \"to\": 2694}, {\"ngram\": \"the police\", \"from\": 2700, \"to\": 2710}, {\"ngram\": \"the house\", \"from\": 2718, \"to\": 2727}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was mistreated, men beat me,\\\" she says quietly.\", \"from\": 2777, \"to\": 2827, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 2796, \"to\": 2799}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The after-effects are still with me.\", \"from\": 2828, \"to\": 2865, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The after-effects\", \"from\": 2829, \"to\": 2846}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But I am still here.\\\"\", \"from\": 2866, \"to\": 2887, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She avoided a death penalty and after 13 months in detention in Toulouse, the 22-year-old Berger was transferred to the Baumettes prison in Marseille.\", \"from\": 2889, \"to\": 3039, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2953, \"end\": 2961, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toulouse\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.720765511182478e-15, \"text\": \"Toulouse\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toulouse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toulouse\"}, {\"begin\": 3009, \"end\": 3025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baumettes_Prison\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Baumettes prison\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baumettes_Prison\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baumettes_Prison\"}, {\"begin\": 3029, \"end\": 3038, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.031877692507295e-20, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a death penalty\", \"from\": 2901, \"to\": 2916}, {\"ngram\": \"13 months\", \"from\": 2927, \"to\": 2936}, {\"ngram\": \"detention\", \"from\": 2940, \"to\": 2949}, {\"ngram\": \"the 22-year-old Berger\", \"from\": 2963, \"to\": 2985}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Members of her group, together with the Resistance, prepared her escape.\", \"from\": 3040, \"to\": 3112, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Members\", \"from\": 3040, \"to\": 3047}, {\"ngram\": \"her group\", \"from\": 3051, \"to\": 3060}, {\"ngram\": \"the Resistance\", \"from\": 3076, \"to\": 3090}, {\"ngram\": \"her escape\", \"from\": 3101, \"to\": 3111}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On October 15, 1943, they came to get her, accompanied by a German soldier who had taken up the cause, while she was in hospital with jaundice.\", \"from\": 3113, \"to\": 3256, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3173, \"end\": 3179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9999963503590359, \"rank\": 3.6427125578611276e-06, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"October\", \"from\": 3116, \"to\": 3123}, {\"ngram\": \"the cause\", \"from\": 3205, \"to\": 3214}, {\"ngram\": \"hospital\", \"from\": 3233, \"to\": 3241}, {\"ngram\": \"jaundice\", \"from\": 3247, \"to\": 3255}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I escaped in my nightdress,\\\" she laughs.\", \"from\": 3258, \"to\": 3299, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my nightdress\", \"from\": 3272, \"to\": 3285}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Once recovered, she campaigned under false identities until the liberation in the summer of 1944.\", \"from\": 3301, \"to\": 3398, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"false identities\", \"from\": 3338, \"to\": 3354}, {\"ngram\": \"the liberation\", \"from\": 3361, \"to\": 3375}, {\"ngram\": \"the summer\", \"from\": 3379, \"to\": 3389}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After the war, she married Lucien Volle, another Resistance fighter who had taken part in the liberation of Le Puy-en-Velay.\", \"from\": 3399, \"to\": 3523, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the war\", \"from\": 3405, \"to\": 3412}, {\"ngram\": \"Lucien Volle\", \"from\": 3426, \"to\": 3438}, {\"ngram\": \"another Resistance fighter\", \"from\": 3440, \"to\": 3466}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 3481, \"to\": 3485}, {\"ngram\": \"the liberation\", \"from\": 3489, \"to\": 3503}, {\"ngram\": \"Le Puy\", \"from\": 3507, \"to\": 3513}, {\"ngram\": \"Velay\", \"from\": 3517, \"to\": 3522}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Together, the couple began to devote themselves to the work of remembrance.\", \"from\": 3524, \"to\": 3599, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the couple\", \"from\": 3534, \"to\": 3544}, {\"ngram\": \"the work\", \"from\": 3575, \"to\": 3583}, {\"ngram\": \"remembrance\", \"from\": 3587, \"to\": 3598}]}, {\"sentence\": \"READ MORE Botswana offers to send Germany 20,000 elephants Genetic clues to left-handedness revealed European pasta market beats to Turkish durum Born in Austria in 1921 into a Jewish working-class family, Melanie Berger began her activism as a teenager in an extreme left-wing group.\", \"from\": 3601, \"to\": 3889, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3636, \"end\": 3643, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9999999682722779, \"rank\": 3.168426018117305e-08, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 3736, \"end\": 3743, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkish_people\", \"score\": 0.9997678869044623, \"rank\": 0.00022017504518313268, \"text\": \"Turkish\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkish_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkish_people\"}, {\"begin\": 3759, \"end\": 3766, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_State_of_Austria\", \"score\": 0.9790605058025131, \"rank\": 0.02136701535167666, \"text\": \"Austria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_State_of_Austria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_State_of_Austria\"}, {\"begin\": 3782, \"end\": 3788, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jews\", \"score\": 0.8633171704587289, \"rank\": 0.13073592367186498, \"text\": \"Jewish\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jews\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jews\"}, {\"begin\": 3811, \"end\": 3818, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melanie_Griffith\", \"score\": 0.5085264710889972, \"rank\": 0.7469599327559292, \"text\": \"Melanie\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/